import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data.dropna(subset=['year'])
    data['year'] = data['year'].dt.year
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    ax = sns.barplot(x="year", y="job_count", hue="sex", data=data)
    ax.axhline(y=data['job_count'].median(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Median')
    ax.legend(loc='upper left')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of job count by sex?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    chart = sns.lineplot(x='year', y='job_count', data=data)
    chart.set(xlabel='Year', ylabel='Job Count')
    plt.title('How has the job count changed over the years?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.sort_values(by='count', ascending=False).head(10)
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    ax = sns.barplot(x="count", y="job", data=data, palette="Blues_d")
    ax.axvline(data['count'].max(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Max count: {data['count'].max():0.2f}")
    ax.legend()
    plt.title("What are the top 10 jobs by count?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data.sort_values(by='year')
    data = data.set_index('year')
    data = data.pivot(columns='job', values='perc')
    data = data.fillna(0)
    plt.stackplot(data.index, data.values.T, labels=data.columns)
    plt.legend(loc='upper left')
    plt.title('What is the percentage distribution of job count by year?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.sort_values(by=['job_count'], ascending=False)
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    sns.set_palette("husl")
    chart = sns.catplot(x="job", y="job_count", hue="sex", data=data, kind="bar", height=6, aspect=1.5)
    plt.title("What is the distribution of job count by job and sex?", wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel("Job")
    plt.ylabel("Job Count")
    plt.legend(title="Sex", loc='upper right')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
